<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-62-0148 </DOCNO><TEXT>In this paper, the authors argue that pursuing a program of space weaponscan eliminate the danger that Soviet nuclear weapons pose for the U.S.The authors say there is another solution to the threat of nuclear war.Instead of having a nuclear freeze, which doesn't make the world anysafer, technology can be used to shoot down intercontinental missilesbefore they hit their targets and destroy American cities. We can makenuclear arsenals obsolete by threatening to protect ourselves, not blowingup the Soviet Union.</TEXT></DOC>